-- Christie’s Appoints Holmberg as Its Head of New York Wine Sales
-- B y   G u y   C o l l i n s
-- 2012-06-20T15:55:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-20/christie-s-appoints-holmberg-as-its-head-of-new-york-wine-sales.html
Per Holmberg is returning to
Christie’s International as head of its  New York  wine
department, having previously worked for the company between
2000 and 2004 in auctions, Christie’s said in an e-mailed
statement.  Holmberg, who will be responsible for wine sales
throughout North and South America, was most recently Vice
President of East Coast operations for Benchmark Wine Group, it
said. He replaces Robin Kelley O’Connor, who left in February.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Guy Collins in London at 
